<h1>Class selectors Demo</h1> 
<p> 
income, expenses, profit are financial terms that are used to measure 
the financial health of a person or a business</p> 
<p class="income"> 
income refers to the amount of miney received by an individual or 
business from various such as employment ,investments or sales of 
goods and service income can be earned on a regular basis such as a 
salary or irregularly such as a bonus are one -time payment</p> 
<p class="expenses"> 
expenses on the other hand, refer to the amount of money spent by an 
individual or business to cover their costs of living or operating.expenses 
can include fixed costs such as rent or salaries variable costs such as 
the cost of materials or discretionary costs such as entertainment or 
travel.</p> 
<p class="profit"> 
profit is the amount of money that remains after deducting expenses 
from income it represents the financial gain or loss that a person or 
business ha generated over a given period of time a positive profit 
means that the income was greater than the expenses while a negative 
profit means that the expenses were greater than yhe income</p> 
<span class="strike"> the current price is 50&#8377; 
</span><span class="red"> and new price is 40&#8377; 
